First Time Instalations:
  - Instructions can be found in mpathic-family-backend-node project

Deployment:
  - SSH (MobaXterm) into EC2
  - cd ~/mpathic/frontend
  - copy the prod folder from your local machine to the EC2 instance using SCP (MobaXterm)
  - cd prod
  - Before running the docker compose command, make sure all images pushed to docker hub are up to date:
    Use docker-compose-dev.yml to build the images locally and push them to docker hub
    The client.ts file should use the production server base URL
  - docker compose down --rmi all (Dangerous command)
  - docker compose up -d --build
  - Usefull commands:
      - docker exec -it <container_id> sh // SSH into a specific container
      - ctrl P + Q // detach from the container shell
Recovery:
  chmod +x frontend_reboot.sh
  sudo crontab -e
  - Add the following line to the crontab file to run the script on reboot:
    @reboot /home/ubuntu/mpathic/frontend/frontend_reboot.sh
  